timeline.bodyText:
I addition to the above use cases, we should probably also support:

The BigInteger.ZERO and BigDecimal.ZERO identifiers

  void zeroConstantBigInt(BigInteger r) {
    BigInteger z1 = BigInteger.ZERO;
    r = r.divide(z1); // Noncompliant
  }

Keeping "ZERO" constraint through "valueOf" from long, double to BigInteger, BigDecimal

  void valueOfBigInt(BigInteger r) {
    long z1 = 0;
    BigInteger z2 = BigInteger.valueOf(z1);
    r = r.divide(z2); // Noncompliant
  }

Keeping "ZERO" constraint through BigDecimal constructor from BigInteger, double, int, long

  void constructorBigDecimal(BigDecimal r) {
    double z1 = 0;
    BigDecimal z2 = new BigDecimal(z1);
    r = r.divide(z2); // Noncompliant
  }

Keeping "ZERO" constraint through "toBigInteger", "toBigIntegerExact", "shortValueExact", "round", "	remainder", "pow", "longValueExact", "longValue" , "	intValueExact", "intValue", "floatValue", "doubleValue", "byteValueExact", "abs", 	shiftLeft, shiftRight
Support 	BigDecimal.divideToIntegralValue like BigDecimal.divide

